However, it is estimated that 10% of cancer cases are caused by heredity.
Several types of cancer remain completely unexplained.
For the Canadian Cancer Association, smoking control remains a priority, despite a decrease in the number of smokers.
Smoking is associated with 85% of lung cancer cases.
It is a risk factor for many others.
It causes enormous harm to people’s health.
"Even today, there are 1.5 million smokers in Quebec," spokesman André Beaulieu said.
10 years after quitting smoking, the risk of dying from cancer is reduced by half.
Weight
