Shimon Ornest: At concerts we want to accumulate positive energy
What do you think about the end of the world in less than a month?
This is just one of the many disturbing news that we humans get so easily.
Together with The Tap Tap, we joke about it all the time and say that we are the only band in the world that can gather enough positive energy to delay or prevent the end of the world.
Moreover, in December you are going to give absolutely unique three concerts against the end of the world.
Can you tell me more about this to the readers?
We are talking about a national fundraising event, which we have been planning for two years.
We decided to take advantage of the marketing potential that the Mayan calendar has, the end of which is announced on December 21 at 11:10.
The day before this event, on December 20, at 21:00, three concerts will start in Prague, Brno and Ostrava.
They will end, roughly speaking, the moment when the May calendar ends on the island of Kiribati in the Pacific Ocean, whose time zone is 12 hours earlier than ours.
Who came up with this idea?
Initially it was my idea, then we all came up with together with our artist Gonza Augusta.
In addition to the fact that we want to accumulate enough positive energy and prevent the end of the world, we also want to think with the public about the state of this world we will one day pass on to our children.
On the occasion of the end of the May calendar, we have created a unique collection of items from shoes, T-shirts, bags and original keys against the end of the world. These things can be bought on the website www.e-tap.cz and thus at the same time provide us with support.
The Tap Tap, along with other musicians, also performed the anthem against the end of the world, which is called "The end of the world is canceled."
Will the already beloved YouTube audience anthem sound at these benefit concerts?
Of course, at the very end, if in the end everything works out and the end of the world does not come.
It will be sung by all the performers at all concerts at the same time.
The anthems will also be played live on Czech television.
The words to this song were written and played the role of Jesus in the video by Tomasz Ganak, also participating in the performance of Xindl X.
How did you start working with them?
We also cooperate with other people of the Czech cultural life, as we hold many charity events and concerts.
We try to actively involve them in these projects.
It turned out that many people like to work with us, they are interested.
Where will the proceeds from the concert against the end of the world go?
For the purchase of equipment for the barrier-free educational center STUDEO, for the sixth year we have been working with the Tap civil association at the Edlichki Institute.
Teachers regularly visit the students of the schools of the Yedlichka Institute and hold fun and interesting events with them.
The students themselves do not have the means to go to the teachers, and in this way we try to provide them with this opportunity.
As part of the additional construction project of the Edlichki Institute, a separate building will appear in the future, in which we will move with this project.
Several musical groups and performers will perform at each concert.
What were the selection criteria?
We tried to create a program that would be of interest to all generations, including children.
For example, in Prague will perform Chinaski, Support Lesbiens, Illustratosphere with Dan Barta, The Tap Tap, Marian Bango and Jiri Suhi.
All details can be found at www.kpks.cz.
