From the very beginning, I felt their potential in the ability to do something extraordinary.
Show business is full of things that imitate each other.
This is logical, everything new is taken with caution, and it lasts for a long time.
There are very few rare things, but I dare say that Tap Tap is one of them.
The first impression of a person who sees us, of course, is pity, it is natural.
But this pity is completely superfluous, because people with disabilities are not some suffering and all the abandoned personalities that we should feel sorry for.
They are people who can live a full life and develop, of course, only if they have the necessary resources.
I say that if people with disabilities succeed, it is a shift not only for them, but for the whole society.
