Each week, students explore apocalyptic topics such as nuclear war, zombies, viruses and bacteria, and global warming.
“We are analyzing why these ideas spread over time,” he said, and the way hypothetical scenarios that trigger certain human actions are suggested.
If nuclear material falls into the hands of terrorists, for example, war could break out.
